 <reference xml:id="ref.xsl" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
  <title>XSL</title>
  <titleabbrev>XSL</titleabbrev>

  <partintro>
   <section xml:id="xsl.intro">
    &reftitle.intro;
    <para>
     L'extension XSL implémente le standard XSL, et fait
     des <link xlink:href="&url.xslt;">transformations XSLT</link> à l'aide de la 
     <link xlink:href="&url.libxslt;">bibliothèque libxslt</link>.
    </para>
   </section>

   <section xml:id="xsl.requirements">
    &reftitle.required;
    <para>
     Cette extension utilise la bibliothèque <productname>libxslt</productname> 
     qui peut être trouvée sur <link xlink:href="&url.libxslt;">&url.libxslt;</link>.
     La bibliothèque <productname>libxslt</productname> version 1.1.0 ou supérieure
     est requise.
    </para>
   </section>

   &reference.xsl.configure;

   <section xml:id='xsl.classes'>
    &reftitle.classes;
    <para>
    </para>

    <section xml:id='xsl.class.xsltprocessor'>
     <title><classname>XSLTProcessor</classname></title>
     <para>
      </para>
     <section xml:id='xsl.class.xsltprocessor.constructor'>
      &reftitle.constructor;
      <itemizedlist>
       <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend='function.xsl-xsltprocessor-construct' /> - construit un nouvel 
        objet XSLTProcessor</para>
       </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
     </section>
     <section xml:id='xsl.class.xsltprocessor.methods'>
      &reftitle.methods;
      <itemizedlist>
       <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="function.xsl-xsltprocessor-get-parameter" /> - Récupère la valeur
        d'un paramètre</para>
       </listitem>
       <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="function.xsl-xsltprocessor-has-exslt-support" /> - Détermine si 
        &php; a le support EXSLT</para>
       </listitem>
       <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="function.xsl-xsltprocessor-import-stylesheet" /> - Importe
        une feuille de style</para>
       </listitem>
       <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="function.xsl-xsltprocessor-register-php-functions" /> - Active la 
        possibilité d'utiliser les fonctions &php; comme fonctions XSLT</para>
       </listitem>
       <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="function.xsl-xsltprocessor-remove-parameter" /> - Efface un 
        paramètre</para>
       </listitem>
       <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="function.xsl-xsltprocessor-set-parameter" /> - Défini la valeur
        d'un paramètre</para>
       </listitem>
       <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="function.xsl-xsltprocessor-transform-to-doc" /> - Transforme en 
        un DOMDocument</para>
       </listitem>
       <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="function.xsl-xsltprocessor-transform-to-uri" /> - Transforme en
        une URI</para>
       </listitem>
       <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="function.xsl-xsltprocessor-transform-to-xml" /> - Transforme en
        du XML</para>
       </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
     </section>
    </section>
   </section>
   
   <section xml:id="xsl.examples">
    &reftitle.examples;
    <para>
     Plusieurs exemples dans ce manuel requièrent un fichier XML ainsi qu'un fichier XSL.
     Nous utiliserons <filename>collection.xml</filename> et
     <filename>collection.xsl</filename> qui contiennent ceci :
    </para>
    <para>
     <example>
      <title>collection.xml</title>
      <programlisting role="xml">
<![CDATA[
<collection>
 <cd>
  <title>Fight for your mind</title>
  <artist>Ben Harper</artist>
  <year>1995</year>
 </cd>
 <cd>
  <title>Electric Ladyland</title>
  <artist>Jimi Hendrix</artist>
  <year>1997</year>
 </cd>
</collection>
]]>
      </programlisting>
     </example>
     <example>
      <title>collection.xsl</title>
      <programlisting role="xml">
<![CDATA[
<xsl:stylesheet version="1.0" xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform">
 <xsl:param name="owner" select="'Nicolas Eliaszewicz'"/>
 <xsl:output method="html" encoding="iso-8859-1" indent="no"/>
 <xsl:template match="collection">
  Hey! Welcome to <xsl:value-of select="$owner"/>'s sweet CD collection! 
  <xsl:apply-templates/>
 </xsl:template>
 <xsl:template match="cd">
  <h1><xsl:value-of select="title"/></h1>
  <h2>by <xsl:value-of select="artist"/> - <xsl:value-of select="year"/></h2>
  <hr />
 </xsl:template>
</xsl:stylesheet>
]]>
      </programlisting>
     </example>
    </para>
   </section>
      
   &reference.xsl.constants;
      
  </partintro>

 &reference.xsl.functions;

 </reference>
 
